description:
The Invisible Plane



Aired on 03/23/2012, Narrated by Jonathan Aris



On 8 October 2001, Scandinavian Airlines Flight 686, a McDonnell-Douglas MD-87, carrying 110 people bound for Copenhagen, Denmark, is taking off at Milan's Linate Airport in thick fog. On the runway, it collides with an Air Evex business jet, a Cessna Citation CJ2 carrying four people bound for Paris, France. The airliner suffers major damage and crashes into a building shortly afterwards, all 114 people on board the two aircraft are killed, along with four on the ground.
